      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="400-04B1" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"><hi rend="underline">Vive la bagatelle</hi> seems to have been Swift's constant motto. His active mind seized every opportunity of exemplifying it, as these and other trifles prove.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-line-1"> The sage who said he would be proud&#13;Of windows in his breast,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-line-2"> Because he ne'er one thought allow'dThat might not be confest;</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-line-3"> His window scrawl'd by ev'ry rake,His breast again would cover;</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-400-04B1-line-4"> And fairly bid the Devil takeThe di'mond and the lover.400-04B1   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
